# Visual golden trees (see ./goldens/): only the curated react/ (CI x86) and
# react-local/<arch>/ (local feedback) sets are committed — generated
# exclusively from client-react's renders via its three `:update` scripts and
# update-visual-goldens.yml. Everything else the three visual tiers (react's
# own + solid's assert-only runs) drop next to a golden on mismatch is
# transient debris and must never be committed:
#   - failure artifacts written alongside the compared golden
#     (`<name>-actual.png` / `<name>-diff.png`)
#   - a spec-named dir written DIRECTLY under `__screenshots__/` (e.g.
#     `__screenshots__/visual.spec.tsx/app-credit-1.png`) when a scenario's
#     baseline routing doesn't apply — never a golden; real goldens always
#     have `react/` or `react-local/<arch>/` between `__screenshots__` and the
#     spec dir, so this can't match them.
goldens/**/__screenshots__/**/*-actual.png
goldens/**/__screenshots__/**/*-diff.png
goldens/**/__screenshots__/*.spec.ts/
goldens/**/__screenshots__/*.spec.tsx/
